  "notes": "Old Portuguese (~14thвҖ“16th c. CE). The Portuguese language after the split from Galician, spoken during the Aviz dynasty and early Age of Discovery. Attested: FernГЈo Lopes chronicles (~1380вҖ“1460), Gil Vicente plays (~1465вҖ“1536), Cancioneiro Geral (1516), royal charters. KEY CHANGES FROM GALAICO-PORTUGUESE: (1) Sibilant deaffrication: /ts/вҶ’/s/, /dz/вҶ’/z/ вҖ” the 4-way contrast collapses to 2 (~14thвҖ“15th c.). (2) Vowel reduction beginning (unstressed /e/вҶ’[Йҷ], /o/вҶ’[u]). (3) Nasal vowels fully phonemicised. (4) /dК’/вҶ’/К’/ simplification. (5) /ou/ вҶ’ [o] monophthongisation beginning centrally. (6) /tКғ/ вҶ’ /Кғ/ deaffrication in progress. trema and grave accent start occasionally appearing. Source: Williams (1962), Mattos e Silva (2006), Castro (2006).",
